data.description: Step back in time with this charming 1890’s Queen Anne Victorian, with original woodwork, sweeping stairwell, built-in butler’s pantry, some tin ceilings, pocket doors, hardwood floors throughout and character to spare. Five bedrooms, formal dining room, parlor with gas fireplace and sunny morning room. High ceilings give a spacious feel. Sit in the cozy screened in porch , or on the wrap around porch and take in the Rockwellian feel of the Village. Wrap-around porch has been transformed with gleaming spindles and gingerbread trim , house and two- story carriage house recently painted. Turret forms bay windows down its length and is topped with a verdigris copper spire. Large walkup attic could also be transformed to additional living space, and the second floor of the carriage house could also be used for an art studio or other use. Driveway paved last summer, and roses planted to climb the columns and frame the porch in color and fragrance. Possible BNB, or short term rental near everything the Finger Lakes has to offer.
